Components

When creating interactive documents using Quarto, you can take advantage of a number of existing components from the JavaScript and Observable ecosystems.

The JavaScript libraries ecosystem

Standard library/npm packages

If you want to use JavaScript modules, many NPM modules are directly available as JavaScript modules with the skypack CDN.

import { sequential } from 'https://cdn.skypack.dev/@tensorflow/tfjs';

Observablehq.com modules

Here, we highlight some libraries that are particularly useful in Quarto interactive documents.

Data manipulation: arquero

Arquero is “a JavaScript library for query processing and transformation of array-backed data tables”. If you’ve used Pandas in Python (or especially dplyr in R), arquero will feel familiar. Here, we import Arquero from its Observable modules

import { aq, op } from '@uwdata/arquero';

Plotting: vega-lite / Observable plot

import { vl } from '@vega/vega-lite-api-v5';
